            <b>How to travel to Jerusalem</b>
            <br />
            Jerusalem is one of the oldest, most historical, revered and majestic cities in
            the world. Considered holy to Jews, Muslims and Christians, a visit to Jerusalem
            is unlike any other experience, with its beautiful religious sites, bustling souks
            (outdoor markets), massive stone architecture, and a warm, diverse culture. Here
            is a guide to making the most of a trip to Jerusalem.
            <br />
            <center>
            <img class="img" border="0" width="320" alt="Photo of a calender"src="Images/traveltut/calender.jpg" /></center>
            1.Get a planner or calendar. Plan your vacation!
            See when you are free from work/school. Plan your flight deoending on the weather in Israel.
            Also, do not fly when it is dangerous in Israel.
            <br />
            <center>
            <img border="0" width="320" alt="Photo of a reading" src="Images/traveltut/read.jpg" /><center>
            2. Read about Jerusalem's history. Jerusalem is a city full of historical events.
            Read about it and know the important buildings and ruins. Also, try to learn a few sentences
            in Hebrew or place names in order to communicate better.
            <br />
            <center>
            <img border="0" width="320" alt="Photo of a plane" src="Images/traveltut/plane.jpg" /><center>
            3. Hop on your flight to Israel! Israel is usually hot so there is no need to bring thick fur coats.
            Make sure you convert your money correctly beforehand. Make sure there are no scissors and sharp
            objects in your personal bag which you take on the plane. When you reach the border check you will need to throw them out.
            <br />
            <center>
            <img border="0" width="320" alt="Photo of a places" src="Images/traveltut/places.jpg" /><center>
            4. Go out and Explore! Don't be afraid to do something unplanned. Jerusalem is full of suprises and
            fun. Make sure you visit the Jerusalem Market. Make the most out of your trip. Enjoy!
            <br />
